# otak-conference Project Rules and Understanding

## Project Overview
otak-conference is a real-time translation conference application that enables multilingual communication using WebRTC and Gemini API with advanced features including emotion recognition, generative art backgrounds, and FIFO audio streaming.

## Architecture
- **Frontend**: React (TypeScript) with Tailwind CSS - **MODULAR ARCHITECTURE**
- **Backend**: Cloudflare Workers with Durable Objects - **MODULAR ARCHITECTURE**
- **Real-time Communication**: WebRTC for audio/video, WebSocket for signaling
- **Translation**: Google Gemini API for speech-to-text and translation
- **Live Audio Translation**: Gemini 2.5 Flash Native Audio Dialog for real-time audio translation
- **Visual Effects**: WebGL-based generative art background with emotion-reactive particles
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages for static frontend, Cloudflare Workers for backend

### Frontend Modular Architecture
- **main.tsx**: Application entry point and DOM mounting
- **components.tsx**: UI components and JSX structure
- **hooks.ts**: Custom hook useConferenceApp with WebRTC/WebSocket logic
- **types.ts**: Interface and type definitions (Participant, Translation, Emotion, etc.)
- **gemini-live-audio.ts**: Gemini Live Audio streaming with FIFO buffering system
- **gemini-audio-processor.ts**: Hybrid audio processing for remote participants
- **emotion-recognition.ts**: Real-time emotion analysis using Gemini 2.5 Flash API
- **generative-art-background-webgl.tsx**: WebGL particle system with emotion-reactive colors
- **translation-prompts.ts**: Comprehensive multilingual translation prompt management (25+ languages)
- **gemini-utils.ts**: Audio processing utilities (PCM conversion, base64 encoding)
- **log-utils.ts**: Centralized logging with JST timestamps

### Backend Modular Architecture
- **worker.js**: Lightweight WebSocket signaling server
- **room-handler.js**: Durable Object class for WebSocket room management
- **Benefits**: Clear separation of concerns, GitHub Pages serves frontend, Cloudflare handles signaling
- **Deployment**: Frontend on GitHub Pages, Backend signaling on Cloudflare Workers
- **CI/CD**: Automated deployment via GitHub Actions to both platforms
- **Domain**: otak-conference-worker.systemexe-research-and-development.workers.dev

## Key Features Implemented

### 1. User Interface
- **Language**: All UI text in English
- **Default Language**: Vietnamese (configurable from 25+ supported languages)
- **Title**: "otak-conference" with "Translation Conference" subtitle
- **Favicon**: Monochrome SVG globe icon with speech bubble dots
- **Design**: Dark theme with gray-900 background and emotion-reactive WebGL particles

### 2. Settings Management
- Auto-show settings panel when username or API key is missing
- Settings stored in localStorage
- Manual toggle via settings icon in header

### 3. Conference Controls
- **Footer Layout**: 3-column grid
  - Left: Start/Close Conference button
  - Center: Mic (with audio settings), Screen Share, Camera, Hand Raise, Reactions, Chat, Emotion buttons
  - Right: Share button (always visible)
- Media controls disabled before conference start
- Visual feedback for active states (colors, opacity)
- Interactive buttons:
  - Hand Raise: Toggle to indicate wanting to speak
  - Reactions: Opens emoji selection popup (👍, ❤️, 😊, 👏, 🎉)
  - Chat: Fully functional real-time chat with read receipts and audio notifications
  - Emotion: Brain icon for emotion recognition toggle

### 4. Room Sharing
- Query string format: `?roomId=uuid`
- Share button triggers copy to clipboard
- Modal notification for successful copy
- Room URL dynamically generated based on current page URL

### 5. Audio Features
- **Microphone**: Default muted on conference start with audio device selection
- **Audio settings modal** (Settings icon on microphone):
  - Microphone device selection with live switching
  - Speaker/headphone device selection
  - Device refresh functionality
  - Real-time device switching during conference
  - Permission-based device enumeration for accurate labels
- **Raw Audio Toggle**: Option to send original audio alongside translated audio

### 6. Chat System
- **Real-time messaging**: Instant chat with all participants
- **Message persistence**: Chat history maintained during conference
- **Read receipts**: ✓ Delivered / ✓✓ Read status indicators
- **Unread counter**: Badge showing unread message count
- **Auto-read marking**: Messages marked as read when chat panel is open
- **Enter key support**: Send messages with Enter or Send button
- **Timestamp display**: Each message shows sender and time
- **Audio notifications**: message.mp3 plays for incoming messages (70% volume)
- **Real-time sync**: Message delivery and read status via WebSocket

### 7. Speaking Indicators
- **Real-time audio detection**: Web Audio API analyzes microphone input
- **Visual feedback**: Green microphone icon with pulse animation
- **Speaking threshold**: Audio level detection with configurable sensitivity
- **Mute consideration**: No speaking indication when microphone is muted
- **Live synchronization**: Speaking status broadcast to all participants
- **Participant list integration**: Speaking indicators appear next to names

### 8. Language Support
- **Supported Languages**: 25+ languages including:
  - European: English, French, German, Italian, Spanish, Portuguese, Dutch, Swedish, Russian
  - Asian: Japanese, Chinese, Traditional Chinese, Korean, Vietnamese, Thai, Hindi
  - Middle Eastern: Arabic, Hebrew
- Language codes use camelCase naming convention
- Default language: Vietnamese
- **Advanced Translation Prompts**: Language-specific system prompts prevent English defaulting

### 9. State Management
- `isConnected`: WebSocket connection status
- `isInConference`: Conference participation status (separate from connection)
- `isGeminiSpeaking`: Gemini speaking state tracking
- Prevents UI flickering during temporary disconnections

### 10. Hybrid Audio Processing System
- **Dual Processing Approach**:
  - **Local Audio**: Uses `GeminiLiveAudioStream` (Live Audio API) for real-time processing with low latency
  - **Remote Audio**: Uses `GeminiAudioProcessor` (standard Gemini API) for transcription and translation
- **Model Configuration**:
  - Live Audio: `models/gemini-2.5-flash-preview-native-audio-dialog`
  - Standard API: `models/gemini-2.5-flash-preview-05-20`
- **Gender Detection and Voice Selection**:
  - Automatic gender detection from participant names using Gemini API
  - Voice mapping: Female→Zephyr, Male→Charon, Unknown→Rasalgethi
  - Integrated into `GeminiAudioProcessor` for TTS implementation

### 11. FIFO Continuous Streaming Audio System (Advanced)
- **Problem Solved**: Complete resolution of choppy audio (プツプツ音) through advanced FIFO buffering
- **Algorithm**: FIFO (First-In-First-Out) queue with intelligent chunk combining for seamless playback
- **Implementation**: `gemini-live-audio.ts` with URL query-configurable parameters for real-time optimization

#### **FIFO System Architecture**:
- **Smart Buffering**: Large buffer capacity (1500 chunks ≈ 60 seconds) prevents overflow
- **Chunk Combining**: Multiple small chunks (default 12 ≈ 480ms) combined for smooth playback
- **Instant Response**: Minimum buffer (1 chunk) for immediate audio start
- **Precise Timing**: 0.25s latency buffer for optimal scheduling accuracy

#### **URL Query Parameter Configuration**:
- **Real-time Tuning**: Adjust FIFO parameters via URL without code changes
- **Available Parameters**:
  - `minBuffer`: Minimum chunks before streaming starts (default: 1, range: 1-20)
  - `maxBuffer`: Maximum buffer size (default: 1500, range: 10-2000)
  - `latency`: Latency buffer in seconds (default: 0.25, range: 0.05-1.0)
  - `combineSize`: Chunks to combine per playback (default: 12, range: 1-20)

#### **Optimal Configuration** (User-tested):
```
?minBuffer=1&maxBuffer=1500&latency=0.25&combineSize=12
```
- **Result**: Completely eliminates audio chopiness with optimal responsiveness
- **Applied as Default**: These values now serve as system defaults for all users

### 12. Emotion Recognition System
- **Real-time Emotion Analysis**: Automatic facial expression analysis using Gemini 2.5 Flash API
- **Visual Integration**: Emotion-based background particle color changes via WebGL
- **Emotion Button**: Brain icon (size 11px) with #2563eb color, matching other control buttons
- **Analysis Frequency**: Every 3 seconds when camera is active
- **Supported Emotions**: happy, sad, angry, surprised, neutral, fearful, disgusted
- **Participant Display**: Emotion emojis shown next to participant names
- **API Token Tracking**: Full integration with usage monitoring system
- **WebSocket Sync**: Emotion data shared with all participants in real-time

### 13. Generative Art Background System
- **WebGL Implementation**: High-performance particle system using WebGL shaders
- **Emotion-Reactive**: Particle colors change based on detected emotions
- **Perlin Noise**: Advanced noise algorithm for natural particle movement
- **Flow Fields**: Dynamic particle attraction and movement patterns
- **Performance Optimized**: Efficient GPU-based rendering
- **Particle Properties**: Age, lifespan, velocity, color attributes
- **Real-time Updates**: Smooth transitions between emotion states

### 14. Interactive Features
- **Hand Raise**:
  - Yellow-highlighted button to indicate wanting to speak
  - Hand icon displayed in participants list when raised
  - Real-time synchronization across all participants
- **Reactions**:
  - Emoji reactions popup with 👍, ❤️, 😊, 👏, 🎉
  - Reactions displayed next to participant name for 3 seconds
  - Animated bounce effect for visual feedback
- **Chat System**:
  - Fully functional real-time chat with read receipts
  - Messages include sender name and timestamp
  - Read status indicators (✓ Delivered / ✓✓ Read)
  - Unread message counter badge
  - Enter key or Send button to submit messages
  - Chat panel toggles from right side
  - Persistent message history during conference
  - Auto-read marking when chat panel is open
  - Audio notification for incoming messages
- **Speaking Detection**:
  - Real-time audio level monitoring
  - Visual speaking indicators in participant list
  - Web Audio API-based detection with threshold sensitivity
- **Real-time Broadcasting**: All interactive features synchronized via WebSocket

### 15. API Usage Tracking
- **Comprehensive Monitoring**: Input/output token tracking for text and audio
- **Session vs Total**: Separate tracking for current session and cumulative usage
- **Cost Calculation**: Real-time cost estimation based on token usage
- **Integration**: Emotion recognition and audio processing contribute to usage stats
- **UI Display**: Usage statistics visible in interface

### 16. Advanced Logging System
- **Centralized Logging**: `log-utils.ts` provides consistent logging across all modules
- **JST Timestamps**: All logs include precise Japanese Standard Time with milliseconds
- **Module Prefixes**: Each component uses consistent prefixes ([Gemini Live Audio], [Conference], etc.)
- **Performance Tracking**: Detailed logs for audio processing and API calls
- **Debug Support**: Comprehensive error logging with context

## Development Workflow
1. Make changes to modular files (main.tsx, components.tsx, hooks.ts, types.ts, etc.)
2. Run `npm test` to ensure all unit tests pass
3. Run `npm run test:api` to test deployed API integration
4. Run `npm run test:integration` to test Gemini Live Audio integration
5. Run `npm run test:all` to run all tests
6. Run `npm run build` to bundle with esbuild (main.tsx entry point)
7. Commit and push to trigger GitHub Actions
8. Automated deployment and testing:
   - GitHub Pages deployment for frontend
   - Cloudflare Workers deployment for backend
   - **Automated API integration testing post-deployment**

